Subject: Six Problem Periphery Inquiry Order

Description: Ordered proof-inquiry route for the six remaining Millennium problem spaces, using periphery probing to shape propositions before proof claims.

& [InquiryOrder] is the working order selected from prior approach-fit analysis
  + [order_001] is Birch and Swinnerton-Dyer
  + [order_002] is Navier-Stokes Existence and Smoothness
  + [order_003] is Hodge Conjecture
  + [order_004] is P versus NP
  + [order_005] is Yang-Mills Existence and Mass Gap
  + [order_006] is Poincare Conjecture
  + [excluded_problem] is Riemann Hypothesis

& [PeripheryInquiryMethod] is the active probing method
  + [trigger_source] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\PeripheryInquiryCuriosityTrigger.sop
  + [dimensional_probe] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\PeripheryDimensionalProbe.sop
  + [correlation_scan] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\PeripheryCorrelationPotentialScan.sop
  + [sectioned_periphery] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric.sop
  + [deep_research_priority_gate] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\research\Deep_Research_Priority_Gate.sop

  = must: start each problem with named focal subject, intended mathematical purpose, and imported-document proposition
  = must: divide internal periphery from external periphery
  = must: classify curiosity triggers before promoting signals
  = must: test candidate dimensions for distinctness, subject fit, evidence fit, and caution load
  = must: route high-curiosity low-resolution formal understanding through deep research before proof-shaping dependence
  = must: adjust proposition shape as proof obligations become clearer
  = must: demote attractive meanings that fail formal mapping or evidence tests
  - never: promote resonance, heat, or metaphor into proof

& [ProofShapeLifecycle] is the development route
  + [stage_001_problem_shape] is define the formal problem boundary and intended proof target
  + [stage_002_document_proposition] is extract the source document's implied proposition
  + [stage_003_periphery_probe] is inspect adjacent concepts, analogues, support gaps, and possible anchors
  + [stage_004_receptive_form] is rewrite the proposition in a tighter inspectable form
  + [stage_005_proof_obligation_map] is name what a proof would need to show
  + [stage_006_adjustment] is strengthen, narrow, split, or retire the proposition according to evidence

& [CurrentFocus] is the active lane
  + [problem] is Navier-Stokes Existence and Smoothness
  + [focus_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\project_reflections\2026-06-27_navier_stokes_current_cycle_component_mapping_001.sop
  + [previous_problem] is Poincare Conjecture
  + [previous_status] is model_boundary_verified
    = first_lock: no_new_poincare_proof_work_symbolic_ricci_flow_is_model_only
  + [next_handle] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\Navier_Stokes_Projection_Remainder_Admission_Gate.sop
  + [next_question] is decide whether to run targeted deep research for velocity-enstrophy-to-pressure projection smallness or mark this Navier-Stokes reentry saturated
